# Cloudinary Configuration
# -------------------------
# To enable photo uploads, you need to provide your Cloudinary account details here.
# These values are public and are used for client-side uploads.

# How to find your Cloudinary Cloud Name:
# 1. Log in to your Cloudinary account dashboard.
# 2. On the main Dashboard page, look for "Account Details".
# 3. Your "Cloud Name" will be listed there. Copy it and paste it below.
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME="drtyzhdhr"

# How to find or create your Upload Preset:
# 1. In your Cloudinary account, go to Settings (gear icon ⚙️) > Upload.
# 2. Scroll down to the "Upload presets" section.
# 3. You can use an existing preset (like 'ml_default') or create a new one by clicking "Add upload preset".
# 4. VERY IMPORTANT: Click on the preset name to edit it. Find the "Signing Mode" setting and make sure it is set to "Unsigned".
# 5. Copy the name of that preset and paste it below.
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLOUDINARY_UPLOAD_PRESET="YOUR_UPLOAD_PRESET"
